OL,3,C'You never heal' ` families still
OL,4,Cgrieving decades after Glasgow murders
OL,6,FThe 26-year-old was last seen alive at
OL,7,Fthe corner of Bothwell Street and
OL,8,FBlythswood Street, in the city's red
OL,9,Flight district.
OL,11,FHer body was found the next day in a
OL,12,Flayby in the village of Bowling, West
OL,13,FDunbartonshire, wrapped in a home-made
OL,14,Fcurtain.
OL,16,FA few years later a man was charged
OL,17,Fwith her murder after his DNA was
OL,18,Fmatched to traces found on Ms
OL,19,FGallagher's clothing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774832614
OL,3,C'You never heal' ` families still
OL,4,Cgrieving decades after Glasgow murders
OL,6,FHowever, a jury returned a not proven
OL,7,Fverdict after a trial in 2004, and Ms
OL,8,FGallagher's murder remains unsolved.
OL,10,F"I think her last words would have
OL,11,Fbeen mammy, I do," Ms Wilson said.
OL,13,F"I think she would have cried out
OL,14,Fmammy and it was more than 100 blows
OL,15,Fshe took.
OL,17,F"Can you imagine that? A wee lassie.
OL,19,F"Then he bit her, he bit her as well.
OL,20,FI don't know. Disgusting. An animal."
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@RO]uD@AOUyD@AOU{D@AOU|D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
